we had very high expectations for this place, which unfortunately fell short.

we really enjoyed the beef and abalone dishes, those were really well done. i also really loved their desserts - that was quite a standout. apart from these, the other courses were good but just did not really hit the spot the same way.

what left a bad impression was the rate at which food was served, it was extremely slow. we felt that the restaurant was handling more customers than it could and couldn‚Äôt keep up. also, we had to wait for awhile for a turn to use the restroom. this is a small issue, but rather unexpected.

that aside though, the service crew was really amazing and professional. they were really knowledgeable and went out of their way to serve us.

overall, it was a fairly pleasant experience although it didnt quite live up to its two star michelin rating. for its price especially, we‚Äôve had better experiences at other places.

text: Usually will have chicken rice from another restaurant nearby, but they are closed between 2.30pm to 5pm today, I just dabao from Five Star Kampung Chicken as I have not tried theirs before. A lot of small sharp chipped bones and not much meat.  Rice is soft but somehow salty think due to too much soya sauce added.

The chicken served at this stall is more tender than most Hainanese chicken rice stalls, which says a lot about the quality since there are many good chicken rice stalls in SG. Coupled with the ultra smooth porridge, this dish is easily one ‚Ä¶

This place is seriously underrated! I went for lunch today (weekday) and there were only three tables occupied, probably mostly guests staying at the Artyzen hotel. Maybe there are not that many people willing to pay fine dining prices for Asian fusion, or the restaurant is still under the radar in terms of publicity.
Personally, I thoroughly enjoyed my lunch - every dish was creative and thoughtfully put together. It‚Äôs the best modern Southeast Asian fusion I‚Äôve had. My favourite was the green lip abalone starter, the herbal brown butter sauce was beautifully aromatic, with a lovely charred note and not overly sweet. The yellow sauce on the yellowtail kingfish main was also fantastic, as were the various garlic based sauces served with the wagyu. Everything was so well-balanced and full of flavor. And the green chili ice cream was refreshingly unique. You can really tell that every component on each plate was crafted with care and intention by the chefs. The service was also warm and attentive, which made the whole experience more enjoyable.
Highly recommended. I‚Äôd love to come back when the menu updates.

All Putien restaurants are very child-friendly and they are very generous to provide full kid's meal which is adult's portion! Food here is up to the Putien restaurant standard üëçüèª

This was going to be a food review but I'm going to talk about an Japan Hour episode.

Tam Jai decided to open in Japan. However, due to the pandemic, the HK founder was unable to fly into Japan to do a taste test to certify the quality before allowing them to open.

What's worse is that the seasoning and soup base ingredients used in HK are not easily available in Japan. There was much R&D and back and forth. Japan had to improvise and send recipes to HK for HK side to replicate to see if the broth is good enough. There were so much details, from taking order, to cooking and ingredients consequence. Watch until stressed üò•

Don't worry as there is a happy ending. If you are ever in Japan and spotted Tam Jai, be thankful that they succeeded and Japanese locals and visitors alike can enjoy the noodles.

I can say that San Suan base is my favourite even though my spice tolerance is low. I think it's their signature base because of the name.

Had dinner there. Atmosphere was good. It was great that we couldn't hear the hustle and bustle of the busy traffic despite being situated right by the main  road. We ordered pani puri and ghee dosas along with filter coffees. The pani puri's filling were ice cold and felt like they were taken out from the fridge minutes ago. I understand its a snack meant to be served at room temperature but definately not cold. The dosas were crisp and nice but nothing different from the other stores you can get just around the corner. The price point is on the higher side and based on my experience you're paying for the atmosphere and the service not so much for the food.

Absolutely loved the beetroot gazpacho with burrata (never tried anything like that before and taste still lingers in my mind). The angels hair pasta with raw prawns is delicious and the prawns used are so sweet! Would definitely be back again to try more of the menu.

text: Pretty little place with lovely service staff and nice food. The fish dish was awesome, and the pork was melt in your mouth. Highlight for me was the dessert: lemon curd tart with preserved lemon. Something different but tasted so good. Will be back again. Cos I love this pretty place.

business_name: Boon Lay Traditional Hakka Lui Cha
text:
It was my first time having thunder tea rice and I took away from this popular stall in Boon Lay.

I was v surprised that it's not as bad as it looks? No "grass taste" for one üòÖüòÇ

In fact, it just tastes like bibimbab/fried rice w a lot of vegetables, which give a nice bite. It's nice both w and w/o the tea soup but I prefer the latter. The coriander and mint leaves in the tea soup are not overpowering and for someone who doesn't like coriander, I think it's still palatable.

Verdict: Will eat again.

A Parisian Escape in Singapore: Revisited

This charming restaurant, conveniently located near Shaw Centre, has captured my ‚Ä¶
Went for dinner during a long weekend. The restaurant was crowded so reservation is recommended. ‚Ä¶

Great dining experience, I enjoyed the creative and tasty dishes. The environment was luxurious and cozy, making it perfect for special occasions. Service was impeccable, with friendly and attentive staff. The deconstructed dishes were most interesting! They don‚Äôt look like their original form, but the chef made a harmonious blend of taste and texture. Try guessing the ingredients!

Service is exceptional. The waitress Yvonne service is commendable! She literally cover few tables and very attentive to the guests needs.

Peking duck is recommended but it is too much for 2 person. The roast pork is good.

Springleaf is definitely my go-to place for prata. A huge variety of prata flavours and unique creations every year. It's always exciting to be able to try new and creative flavours that has been curated with wonderful ideas. I always come ‚Ä¶

Incredible experience from Wai Leong and his team. Everything was flawless from beginning to end. We saved this as our last meal of our trip and we both said it was our favourite. A key part was that the restaurant is small enough that everything feels personalised without feeling awkward. The chefs were so knowledgable and friendly, their passion for the dishes was definitely infectious throughout the sitting. We were lucky enough to sit at the counters so we could watch the chefs and ask questions about the dishes, which were incredible and perfectly balanced for 6 courses. The food was delicious and completely different to anything else we‚Äôd eaten on our trip. The quality was unmatched!
If you‚Äôre planning a trip to Singapore or you‚Äôre a local, this restaurant absolutely must be on your list to visit. Thank you!
Nice place, good food - mushroom soup tasted yummy and beef was cooked nicely and great flavour.  Vasan's personal touch is icing on the cake.

The satisfaction with the service of this restaurant started during my planning 2 months before the actual visit. The staff remembered and noted every allergy and preference detail, and provided all the assistance needed for the reservation. On the day of visit, I'm pleasantly surprised with the amuse bouche, the texture of the different items on the plate, the taste, the flavours that blend so well together. The entire dinner was divine. I never had to ask for water top-up once, the service crew was so observant that before I finished my glass of water, he was there to top it up. Excellent! Will definitely recommend!
Amazing pasta , especially the truffle cream handmade pasta love it!

Lovely, cosy restaurant with great service. Food is elevated fusion chinese, and is a more premium fine dining style.  We went for the 2pax Anyi set and I loved the ceviche, spinach mushroom and beef short ribs. Unfortunately, the seabass was not available when we went. Happy hour 1 for 1 lasts between 5-7pm.
First time trying Sri Lanka cuisine. Tasty but some dishes can be a tad salty. All items ordered were good.

As always, great food & even greater service
Shout-out to the team & Rui that were taking care of our table. In addition to that, Jia Yi ,& Bing Yi too for their welcoming warmth ‚Ä¶

Thanks Nono for the patience in explaining the menu and recommending the fried carrot cake with eggs, love the dishes. Will definitely come back üëç

Cinder never fails to uphold their quality in their ingredients and preparation. We always enjoy the food, the sides are delicious in addition to the steak.
The mashed potatoes are sublime.
I had the lunch set this visit and it was very reasonably priced for 3 courses and the tarte au Citron was beautiful in flavour and presentation.
The service is always top notch, polite and prompt.
Water is pricey, however, at $7 a bottle and I did not appreciate the taste of the fancy water.

The famous beef hor fun was excellent as usual, the fried rice and dim sum were equally v good! Best of all they don‚Äôt charge the 10% service charge which makes meals here rather great value! The original shop in Geyland now extended to the west side.

Great ramen fix in a place where food options are generally lacking!

The broths are rich and wholesome, collar chashu very tenderly done, belly ‚Ä¶

This is the kind of place you walk past many times before realising you‚Äôve been missing something solid. It‚Äôs a true hole in the wall izakaya that opens for lunch and dinner.

We ordered edamame, Japanese omelette, agadeshi tofu and rounds of nigiri sushi. Everything was fresh and unfussy. Service was a bit slow when things got a little busy, but the host was always polite. Overall good value for money if you‚Äôre looking for a change from donki!
Second time here, food is still as good and love the atmosphere best! Service by Xuan and Josh were great as well. ‚Ä¶

Spent a lovely company lunch at Colony today. First, I was greeted by Bastien who assisted me with my bag. He was very chatty and lively. Next I had trouble finding the entrance and confused it with Republic as it was my first time there. A ‚Ä¶
Would prefer self service kiosk just like Raffles Place outlet, no need to face the rude cashier.
Mac food as usual but it's crowded esp in the evenings. Btw the parking driveways are very confusing though there's ample parking spaces.

The portions were generous and the food is nice. The chili is absolutely tasty and goes so well with the rice. Personally, I prefer the sweeter curry as gravy over the rice. Only downside for me is the cracker is not as crunchy. Will definitely come back again.

Marguerite offers a serene ambiance, warm service, and vibrant drinks, setting the stage for the true stars: the exquisite dishes crafted by chef-owner Michael Wilson. From his trio of open kitchen islands, Chef Wilson presents a culinary ‚Ä¶

Dining at Mr. Lun‚Äôs place is a truly pleasant and memorable experience. From the moment you arrive, you can feel the genuine hospitality and dedication to service. Mr. Lun himself is incredibly service-oriented‚Äîhe pays close attention to ‚Ä¶

business_name: Sen Sen Sushi Jem by DON DON DONKI Singapore
text: Our experience was just OK. The initial impression was that it would be a cheaper Japanese restaurant, as it is by Don Don Donki, but it wasn't. Our lunch bill for 2 adults and a toddler worked out to $90, and we didn't order any alcohol or ‚Ä¶

Absolutely fantastic. Every dish we had felt perfectly balanced, not too salty, with lovely and fresh flavours. Maybe we got lucky with our order? The place has extremely limited seating and the queue can get crazy, but I see what the wait is about. Don‚Äôt know what the other reviewers are smoking; this place is good!

This is a new vegetarian restaurant replacing the previous owner. Their renovation and set up is really nice & cosy. Their food is delicious and their service is very friendly. They also have a little corner selling vegetarian ingredients. Love this place üòã ‚Ä¶
We were attended to and served by Ansyari, who was friendly and very helpful, especially with our takeaway requests. ‚Ä¶

The chicken is superb! Meat texture is cook to near perfect... even the tricky chicken breast taste great! Soaked in its savoury soy sauce, coupled with silky smooth Cantonese style porridge... slurpp~~~~~ ah... Oishi ne...

business_name: Baguo Grilled Fish Â∑¥ÂõΩÁÉ§È±º - 154 West Coast
text: We ordered only 3 items but was so full from it! Spent only $60 and was extremely satisfied with the quality of the food. Fish is fresh and full of ingredients. Fried noodles is delicious, flavourful and full of wok hey. I truly enjoy their soup which does not make me very thirsty after that. Have purchase the credit. Look forward to come again!

Came here for a birthday dinner with a group of 5, and overall, the food was quite good. The steak and lamb ribs were cooked perfectly, and the mashed potatoes were a nice complement. However, the sauce was a bit on the salty side. Everyone enjoyed their meals, and the desserts were delicious‚Äînot overly sweet, which was a nice touch.

The downside was the lack of proper steak knives. We were given butter knives to cut through the steak and lamb ribs. When we asked, we were told that they had just added these dishes to the menu and were still waiting for steak knives to arrive. While understandable, it would have been better if they had waited for the knives before launching the new dishes or at least informed customers of the situation and maybe offered to assist with cutting.

The prices are a bit on the steep side, but for a special occasion, it's worth it, especially since the food was enjoyable overall.

Came here for lunch to celebrate my wife's birthday, the pizza is definitely better than the pasta, and the sweets are absolutely amazing. The service team is also very friendly, attentive and made the effort to make us feel special. 5 stars for the team.

the man manager is very rude. firstly, he wears ‚Äúmask‚Äù while working in an f&b establishment with the mask half on his face with mouth exposed and talking to his fellow colleagues in the store. Do you not know that saliva can fly? Hasn‚Äôt covid already happened? Second, saw a cockroach at the table beside. Ew. Last time it was always full house and bustling. Now? Looks like a far cry from the past. Standards really horrible. Prices inflated like mad. Service horrible.

This is my Second visit to this Amazing place. Honestly I should say that I came from Sri Lanka recently and this restaurant is the best restaurant which I found in Singapore so far
I mean you can taste one of the best. Delicious Indian ( same like Sri Lankan) foods with lot of varieties for very Reasonable price ( honestly I was surprised with prices that they offer for these quality foods and meals sets )

I am expecting to vieit this place at least two times a month since I am very far from here , but still I wanna cone here not only to have good fooods
But to have some good relaxation with this calm and quiet vibe around my table

So thank you owners for providing such good quality service for affordable prices for the people like us

text: I feel its quite nice. But maybe next time can put recommended portion pax cause I am worried about over or under ordering the food for my group.

A truly must return if you are particular about the food! This is actually our 2nd time back here and each dish is simply impressive. Absolutely love the chef‚Äôs use of different spices to bring out the taste of each main ingredient.

Nasi Lemak is piping hot. Really delicious. Queue was already long before it opened.

Chicken wings tasted okay, rendang is great!
Sambal is a little too sweet for my liking.

Nice place to have a quiet meal. Service was good, but waiter seems v anxious to keep clearing the table. Made our meal feel abit rushed. Food was good, beef was decent and tender. Everything was on the pricey side but overall a good experience.

Overall good restaurant.

Good point
Great food with Wine

Improvement point
No menu in homepage
Wines are quite expensive but great selections
Volume- we were told by a lady that appetizer is small for one person. And main dishes are for one person. The reality: main dish lamb was for 4 people portion. Octopus - appetizer is not a small portion. We are average Asians. I felt like I was in US.
Poor Communication - I changed the number of guest from 4 to 3 one week before. But their reservation was still 4. I sent a message of birthday cake plate in advance but no confirmation in advance and no arrangement on the day. Big question - Michelin Star restaurant cannot do this ?
Had an absolutely lovely time with my family here. All the dishes were deliciously unique and creative, with decent portions for the mains. ‚Ä¶

The food was unique and intriguing, with ingredients that were new to me and made for an exciting experience. However, the meal took far too long for my liking‚Äîat least two hours for a lunch course. At times, the gaps between courses felt unnecessarily drawn out; for instance, we often finished one dish but had to wait a while for the next to arrive. Additionally, the service didn‚Äôt feel particularly welcoming or friendly, which dampened the overall experience. While the food itself was memorable, I‚Äôm torn about whether I‚Äôd want to visit again.

Artichoke changed their mezze menu to a mozza menu and dayum‚Ä¶ I was impressed. Sat at the counter and the chef in front had a ‚Äúlet‚Äôs hope this was a good idea‚Äù t-shirt and indeed, I do think it‚Äôs an excellent idea to pivot to pizza. ‚Ä¶

Buona Terra, a Michelin-starred gem in Singapore, offers a dining experience that seamlessly blends exquisite Italian cuisine with an elegant atmosphere. From the moment you step into the restaurant, you're greeted with a warm and sophisticated ambience, setting the stage for a memorable meal.

The menu, a testament to culinary artistry, is a journey through contemporary Italian flavors with a creative twist. Each dish is meticulously crafted, showcasing the freshest ingredients and a perfect balance of flavors. The signature dishes, such as the handmade pasta and the expertly cooked seafood, are a true delight, leaving your taste buds tantalized.

What elevates the dining experience at Buona Terra is the impeccable service. The staff is knowledgeable, attentive, and genuinely enthusiastic about ensuring every guest has a wonderful time. Their recommendations for wine pairings are particularly noteworthy, enhancing the flavors of each course.

The restaurant's intimate setting makes it an ideal spot for special occasions or a romantic evening. The attention to detail in the decor complements the overall sophisticated vibe of the place.

In summary, Buona Terra is a culinary jewel in Singapore's dining scene. Its combination of exceptional Italian cuisine, a warm and elegant setting, and top-notch service rightfully earns its Michelin star and makes it a must-visit for those seeking an extraordinary dining experience.

Very clean and elegant dining room with a great view of the bay area facing Marina Bay Sands.
Service was excellent. ‚Ä¶

Huge disappointment today, as a customer who have been visting the restaurant since 2018, me and my friends always had enjoyed our meals and time at this restaurant. Until today, when I visitted again with my friend for dinner is our WORST eating experience by far.

It all started when we were waiting to be served, we avoided peak hours at around 4:30PM and though there were almost no customer in the restaurant, the staffs were chatting around and no one came to serve though I believe a few of them saw us. It was only until we signalled when one came over. This was still alright for us but already a bad impression. Can tell that the standards have really dropped.

Next we had our meal as per normal, UNTIL when we were about to finish. One of the staff - FAZIL, took the utensils holder straight, took the receipt which was in there and threw it disrespectfully straight at the table. We were stunned and of course unhappy by such action. If he wanted to take the utensils holder, I thought it was a basic courtesy to ask, not only did he not, he threw the receipt straight. What's worst was there were no customers even queing to be served, don't understand why it was so urgent that he had to act as such? I get much better service and respect at hawker centre and coffee shops and I DO NOT even need to pay service charges. I am paying service charges for such service WOW. And guess what? That is not it, he later came back again and took away my glass when my drink was still HALF FILLED. We may have finished our food but does that mean we won't want our drinks anymore? Hello? We paid for the drinks too!

Seems like only prices increase while service decreased SO MUCH. Congrats! You have just lost yourself a group of loyal customers who visit on a constant basis. We may or may not be the first who was dissapointed by such service but if it does not improve and if FAZIL is still serving, there would only be more. Seriously WORST experience ever, I would reccomend my friends and family to avoid visiting this restaurant again and I would NEVER step food into any branch of this restaurant anymore.
Amazing old-school kway chap.. Great value too...

Had a late lunch with my hubby at Gain City, Happy Cafe in in Sungei Kadut.

Halal certified.

I ordered the fish and chips, which came with generous, chunky wedges topped with cheese‚Äîvery tasty! The fish was fresh, though I would have preferred the batter to be a bit crispier. The spicy chili sauce really added a nice kick.

I also had the icy strawberry mint drink, which was super refreshing‚Äîperfect for the hot day.

The only downside was that the air conditioning could only really be felt when the exit doors were closed.

Still, overall, I really enjoyed my meal and the experience. Looking forward to coming back again... and getting my new fan fixed next week! ü§ó

Musollah avail @ Gain City ground flr.

Have a great, authentic and luscious Omakase  dinning experience at Tomidou.. Got to savour the famous Oma bluefin tuna,  Uni (from Hokkaido and generous serving!) and  fish sperm sac which was pleasantly tasty.  Chef Akira was affable and the staff were all so friendly and attentive.. Definitely returning for the Oishiii Omakase again ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

As evidenced by the shop's wall pics, the restaurant's trade-mark artwork prominently highlights a raw chicken-egg (resembling a full moon) atop a hamburger patty, hence its name "moon viewing". Indeed, a very unique and romantic concept!
We ordered 3 signature sets:
*foie gras
*mushroom (kinoko), and
*avocado.
The meat patty was scrumptious and tender to the bite. The tamago (egg) soup was also delightful (not too salty).
(We, as laymen, are puzzled why the industry continues to use the word "steak" for the patty.)
The pricing of the menu items was "pocket-friendly".
It was overall a pleasant lunch outing for us.
Ms Kim Tang, who attended to our table, was hearty and meticulous in her work. Well done!
Ordered a few dishes to try. The truffle omuburg was the best. The beef hamburgs were very nicely cooked, slightly charred with a tinge of sweetness. ‚Ä¶

Been hearing good things about Nalan and a few of us decided to go there for dinner. The menu was rather extensive and we were spoilt for choices, we had the staff recommend us some of their eats. The foods were delicious and flavourful. We enjoyed our dinner. My favourites were the puri and assorted platter.
The queue is ridiculous long, very bad attitude especially the auntie, not recommended stall. They are better chicken rice stall at this hawker centre. Do not visit this outlet.
Very nice sushi at reasonable price

Heavily overrated restaurant, food was just ok but like some reviews said the ingredients were just normal cheap ingredients, nothing special. Portion was small, and by serving it small doesn't guarantee delicacy. Overall not really satisfied with the experience here.

Good environment. Quality of the food doesn‚Äôt match the price.

They have the take and go food, but is abit cold. You can request them to heat up. Dining in can be very pricey.
A very average one-star Michelin restaurant with standard, unremarkable flavors.

Ivins sells nice Peranakan dishes, which I recommend visiting if you want to know how Peranakan food tastes like. It is around 10 to 15 minutes walking distance from King Albert Park MRT Station, so it isn't that nearby

Their Beef Rendang tasted good & soft, and their Honey Pork was good too. Their Chendol tasted a bit different from our usual Chendol at coffeeshops, in a good way. Recommended!

$6.50 Ayam penyet, $5.50 Thai chilli chicken cutlet..
Overall the food is nice and value for money. Teh tarik will be better if more Gao..

Amazing and attentive service by the staff.
Food was authentic and good. ‚Ä¶
Awesome atmosphere, service and food. Impressed with their authentic and fresh dim sum. Flavorful dishes.

Dinner with friends at A-poh kitchen and it is really amazing! Halal Chinese Tze char allows us to have an amazing meal with my muslim friends.

Personally loved the sambal kangkong, prawn paste church the most. Others dishes were decent.

Will come back again if we planning to dine out in that neighbourhood.

And the service was fast and prompt.

Highly recommend

The oysters are to die for. We kept ordering more and more because it was worth it and the quality is incredible.
Shoutout to the shokupan because it was umami-ing.
The crab mafaldine? You can take my card and my bank account and all my assets. The sauce coating the pasta was very lovely. I am 90% sure that the crab stock was boiled for 73 years and 2 months, causing a very rich bold crab flavour but not overpowering. Cucumbers in a pasta? Weird when you read it but it actually pairs so well as it gives a little bit of freshness in every bite, making you feel like eating 1 portion is not enough.

And amazing service! Incredibly friendly and awesome staff. It is very rare to see a restaurant/cafe topping up my water all the time, I swear my glass is half-full, MINIMUM.
Can a meal ever be worth a thousand bucks? I personally didn't think so before, until I tried Zen. ‚Ä¶
Nice made to order sushi place inside Don Don Donki Jurong Point.  Extensive menu and fresh fish - it's a nice alternative of prepared sushi of Don Don Donki. ‚Ä¶

Service is good but food portion is quite small, especially the starter. The fried rice is quite bland actually. Xiao long bao is above expectation but the skin is getting thicker now. If no queue it is ok but if long  queue then no point waiting.

The food was pretty decent. However, the service was really bad, we booked a reservation for 10 people, and when we arrived, there were no seats available. They then forced us to sit in a 7-seater table, which we declined because it was too ‚Ä¶

Restaurant is located in vibrant Keong Saik
Road and is nicely decorated. The rather small setup gives a cosy atmosphere to the place.

We were welcomed by friendly staff who made sure to provide a great service.
Food was simply amazing; starting by an authentic Pissaladi√®re and fresh Burrata to start.

Mains were delicious too; Monkfish tail has a generous serving and is paired with a tasty Chorizo and Ratatouille side. Pastis flamb√©ed Tiger Prawns are generous and divine. Bouillabaisse is served with Rouille sauce exactly like in France.

Desserts were the star of the show Deconstructed Lemon & Meringue pie is well balanced and tasty. Pistachio cr√®me br√ªl√©e is very original and delicious. Strawberry millefeuille is a classic that never disappoint and my dad was thrilled by the Molten cookie with salted caramel sauce.

Having dinner at Loulou was the best way to end 2024 and we will definitely come back for the experience!

I am writing to share feedback regarding my recent dining experience at the Colony buffet this evening, which was intended to be a special occasion as it was my father-in-law's birthday. This visit was particularly disappointing, as it was ‚Ä¶

The food was alright especially if you are looking for something cheap but good. The only problem I had was the staffs there, particularly the staff that has blue hair. She was very rude when me and my friends when we simply asked her nicely if its possible to add on and pay extra to our order due to us clicking wrongly but she answered rudely and said it wasn‚Äôt possible and we were totally okay with that response as we wanted clarification. What I don‚Äôt understand is why does she have to reply to us like that as if we pissed her off when we weren‚Äôt even shouting or yelling at her? From there we lost our appetite. To add on, she was talking very loudly and rudely to her coworkers on how tired she is to ‚Äòentertain‚Äô. I didn‚Äôt know what that means but okay. And then she was yelling loudly again that she is tired and pissed and while saying that, she threw the menu. Maybe she had a bad day or that she faced too many customers that pissed her off, I understand that. But that doesn‚Äôt mean she got to shout and yell emphasising shes tired to entertain people. If she is tired then simply quit the job as an fnb staff and find another job, is that easy. Everyone is working as well but I am pretty sure that they are not complaining out loud especially if they want to earn money. Fix your staff‚Äôs working attitude if not fire her since she complains a lot on what she is suppose to do.

Very disappointing visit. The food is just bad. We ordered the borscht soup, it‚Äôs bland and not nice to drink at all. And the shashlik of beef and shashlik of lamb, both are also bad. The beef had a weird taste and it is cold and rare when ‚Ä¶

Excellent service the team, Manager Vasanth and the team Menn, Chan and others. If you want visit jacks place, i will recommend this Safra Jurong outlet. During the busy time too, they managed well that i have to wait less than 15 minutes. Food service was fast and really good taste. Will visit again. üëåüëå . Very much satisfied.

The view and atmosphere is great. The food is good and well prepared. I did not get condements on the table with my food, as one woild exspect in Europe or anywhere else. But when I asked, I received.

The ambiance is very welcoming the service is unmatched, staff truly cares about your experience and the food was amazing, everything we tasted melted in our mouths. The best meal we have had in awhile. Baraco is highly recommended for an Italian restaurant and the experience you will remember.

business_name: I Love Sukhothai - Limbang Shopping Centre
text:
Came here for dinner and ordered my usual fair so I can do a proper comparison. Tom yum soup was quite good, but the flavour could be better.

Highlights of the place were crab vermicelli and scrambled eggs omelette. Very well done and highly recommended if you visit this place.

Pictures look bluish because I was seated below the lights.

Chanced upon the place after Pandan reservoir run, the service is like sitting in a home run cafe so exquisite. Honey glazed Chicken and waffles were really good. The best thing that I had and brought multiple friends repeatedly is the Baileys Latte. Definitely one of the best lattes both hot and iced, I prefer hot better!

June 2024

I was looking forward to try this restaurant for a long time. I received their ‚Ä¶
My son‚Äôs favourite restaurant, his favorite gindara and soba, at West Coast Plaza Sushi Tei

The newly revamped Japanese food hall has many new and enjoyable choices, from Ramen to Gohan. The Saba Shioyaki Set ($11.90) and Beef Rice Set ($14.90) from My Gohan were both good and the furnishings were refreshing.
Lovely place and very friendly staff.

The overall experience is worthy of 1-star Michellin. The main course (duck) is well delivered. The meat is tender, slightly seasoned to go with beet root sauce and condition. I‚Äôm not particularly impressed with other dishes, perhaps due to personal preferences. In my humble opinion, they could be better. The under-delivery is their pasta cooked in rib sauce, topped with pork cheek and mushroom. Having been to a few dining establishments of similar privilege, I wish their portion can be bigger to allow a sumptous experience.

The zi char food here was great; I ordered 4 different dishes and I liked them all. The overall price was affordable and food was enough for 2 people. I paid cash as they only accept that or CDC vouchers.

We loved every moment of it. The view by the aquarium is the best, the food was on the higher side in pricing but great in quality. Most deserving of praise is the service for sure.

Jeckie our host was impeccable throughout the night, he is such a gem and made the dinner as amazing as it was. Thank you so much for making our night.

My mom is from Penang, very rarely I eat Penang food in SG unless necessary, since my grand aunt invited me, why not ? Free food haha. We actually  over -order as there are 7 of us. In terms of authenticity, the prawn mee (Hokkien mee in Penang) and the Penang laksa stands out, the rest so so,  other dishes is our SG typical tze-char dishes. Overall enjoyable, and fyi we ate everything. Will return next year ! (I live in Tampines)
Affordable pricing... affiable bosses and staffs

Good Food, but More South Indian Vibes

I tried two North Indian thalis and a masala dosa at Nalan Singapore. The food ‚Ä¶
Delicious and large portions with lots of choices.

I think the dim sum in this stall is the best I ever ate in Singapore. Most of dim sum are with fresh shrimp. Shrimp is fresh , juicy and savory. The fried yam rice s so good, the inside filling is like corn soup yam version, creamy and ‚Ä¶

First time being here and tried few famous Hunan dishes, much better than expected and all spicy ones are not that spicy for me which is tasty and delicious but not making you cry when eating those chilies. The fish for me is a bit too crispy? But rest are all good. Will come next time for trying other dishes like shrimp or twice cooked fish!

Famous Nasi Lemak, Nasi Sambal Goreng & Nasi Rawon! Best know for the sambal & selling separately.
We had late breakfast here on 22 Jul 2023. You can see the long Qs from the carpark. Once reached, you will notice 2 long Q & need to ask which Q know serves different types of dashes.
I have long eating at this place as a friend had bought me a packet of Nasi Sambal Goreng with fried chicken üçó üêî.
Next trip will try the Lontong & Mee rebus

This place has become one of my favorite vegan restaurants in Singapore!

Great variety of choices from salads, wraps, burgers, bowls, pizzas, desserts and healthy drinks. Price is reasonable and most of all, the foods are just delicious that we always end up with ordering too muchü§§

If you are looking for something special, try the Truffle Cheeseburger Pizza. It's not a burger (of course!) but you'll be amazed by the nice combination of marinated tempeh, cashew cheese and vegetables.

As for wraps, we've tried the Eggxellent Avo Wrap and Temphetion (Sh)room Wrap. Personally I like the Eggxellent better and the tofu does taste like eggs. By the way the seaweed fries come with the wraps are ridiculously delicious that I even asked if I can order extra (unfortunately not). Hope one day can see them in the menuüôè

There are (too) many options for desserts but finally we chose PB & J Brownie Mudpie. Unlike most of the brownies that have thick/creamy texture, the Mudpie here is more like eating strawberry ice cream in a chocolate tart. The texture is so light that you can finish it in secondsü§£

Will definitely come back and try other menu :)
I had the opportunity of trying 2 dishes here, the chicken and the grilled squid - it did not disappoint. I hear the warung is pretty good as well. ‚Ä¶

A nice little Halal Chinese Cuisine restaurant. Serves good dishes at reasonable price. They have curry fish head and tail promotion which I go for. Good authentic Chinese cooking. We always clean out the plate. The waitresses are attentive and provide good service.

We had a great experience dining at this place, love the interior decor as well as the scrumptious food. It was a birthday celebration, the staffs vr accomodating by keeping the surprise till the end for my fren. All the staffs are excellent and vr helpful. Definitely will be back again

Paradise Dynasty is a popular spot, especially during dinner hours, so it‚Äôs best to make a reservation in advance if you don‚Äôt want to wait.

Food-wise, it‚Äôs generally consistent, though I personally find their noodle dishes to be more reliable than the stir-fry options. My go-to is the dry spicy noodles with pork and prawn dumpling‚Äîit's flavourful without being overly spicy, and always hits the spot.

Their stir-fry dishes can be hit-or-miss. For example, the spinach stir-fry can be well-seasoned on some days but completely bland on others. The stir-fried beef also suffers from this inconsistency.

Appetiser-wise, the black fungus with peppercorn and garlic used to be a favourite, but they seem to have reduced the quality recently, making it tougher to chew. On the other hand, the cucumber with garlic, chilli and vinegar is refreshing and appetising, and the drunken chicken remains flavourful and well-marinated.

Overall, it‚Äôs a good place to pop by, especially if you're craving reliable noodles and decent sides, just manage your expectations with the stir-fry.

I recently visited Nalan Restaurant and was genuinely impressed by the entire experience. The food was rich in traditional Indian flavors, with an impressive variety for different dietary preferences. Each dish‚Äîfrom starters to desserts‚Äîwas ‚Ä¶

This is a 2 Michelin star dining experience. While it is definitely a pricey meal, some of the best fine dining I‚Äôve had was here.

The only qualm I have is that it was slightly tough to understand the waiters when they were explaining our dishes because of accents etc but we managed to understand eventually!

The dishes themselves were all made with the highest ingredients and presented in such an impeccable manner. All of the dishes were balanced and portioned incredibly well and had exquisite components. It‚Äôs an upmarket experience for sure but if you‚Äôre into this kind of thing then you have to pay a visit.

All in all for fine dining Italian you really can‚Äôt go wrong here. Just be prepared to pay for it that‚Äôs all! Wonderful experience.

Went there for an event and had set menu for dinner. Overall the meal is good and excellent. I thought the duck with noodles is good but inappropriate because that 1 full portion is too much. If it was half might be better. Many of us just had 1 mouth and say it too full which is such a waste. Otherwise I think it is ok.

This is one of the most popular BBQ Seafood in the Jurong region to get your Sambal Stingray and Sambal Sotong fix.

Have been coming to this store for more than 20 years (used to be at another market before moving here). The quality and the sambal is still as top notch and consistent throughout the years.

Naturally, due to inflation, prices have increased over the years, but that doesn‚Äôt warrant a drop in stars as everywhere the prices are increasing. For a decent portion of stingray at $16 and sotong at $15, the prices are still considered reasonable.

Good quality, good quantity, average prices and situated in your typical neighborhood hawker centre; worth it and will continue to patronize.

Had an excellent meal with the 1826 team. Was pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food and the service by the team. Kudos for Khun Picha who took care of us. Always making sure we had everything we needed especially when we had 2 ‚Ä¶

Came here with the family as we wanted to have some Chinese cuisine for dinner. As it had been a long time since I came to Jurong Point, I was quite surprised to see this outlet here, which was pretty cozy and surprising packed on a weekday ‚Ä¶

Tried their breakfast, which was yummy with the usual breakfast suspects plus bonus interesting options.  Do try their Kaya French toast with creme anglais. Great service, which is especially hard to find at other establishments on an early weekday morning.

The food was superlative,  really memorable food coma experience of a lifetime... not overstating at all.  Maybe the chef had a super in the zone mode, everything was delightful and excruciatingly tasty!  Had the seabream caparcio, foie gras terrine, croquet madame, steak frites, crepe suzzette, washed down with champagne... definitely a must return!
Very friendly lady boss and yummy yummy food!! Will come here often
Conducted our ROM solemnization at Lawry's followed by lunch for 14 pax, it was a breeze with the Lawry's team! Highly recommend hosting special occasions in their private rooms. ‚Ä¶

Ordered a large steam chicken, small Hong Kong styled fish, small fried french beans, small yang zhou fried rice, small tomato fried egg and large soup of the day. I think it's too much food for 5 pax. ‚Ä¶

Welcoming, courteous, professional and attentive staff. Minimal waiting time for food despite it being almost full house. Delicious value-for-money French cuisine. I appreciated that all the staff kept their masks properly worn throughout the time I was there. To top it off we received a warm greeting from the head chef aka boss himself and his wife, after a little chat they realised it was our 23rd anniversary and as if by magic a pleasant surprise in the form of a complimentary piece of cake with a candle appeared before us! Dining in a restaurant of this calibre is not just about the food but also about the experience. 100 marks for that!

Food was good, and service was great. The service staff (especially Doris!) was super attentive every time we ate at the Jem outlet and made sure our orders were delivered, and that our tea cups were filled. ‚Ä¶
I tried their Red Tom Yum Seafood Tang Hoon as part of their $11.90++ lunch set, and it was absolutely satisfying! The soup was flavorful‚Äîperfectly spicy, tangy, and packed with fresh seafood. ‚Ä¶

The aquarium dining experience was awesome. All the service members were friendly. The aquarium was full of marine lives with Manta rays, hammerhead sharks and etc... The foods was tasty, I like the bread they served together with honey and butter spread. Had enjoyed they dinner very much. Thanks for the servicing team.

Food at Pura Brasa  restaurant is nice Surp delicious , will come back again in near future. Paella seafood is so nice , carbonara pizza also extremely nice. Lamb rack was tender n soft nicely matching the sauce.bread with topped tomatoes surp special. Thank you for arranging a good table for us , deeply appreciated.

Airy, upscale hotel eatery with 7 open kitchens, plus a la carte meals & a generous global buffet.
The Colony buffet at the Ritz-Carlton is generally considered a top-tier buffet ‚Ä¶

business_name: Baguo Grilled Fish Â∑¥ÂõΩÁÉ§È±º - 154 West Coast
text:
This is my first visit to this restaurant. The staff are friendly. Just 2 of us, so we couldn‚Äôt order too many dishes to try. The ÊâãÊíïÂåÖËèúwas not so oily , and taste was light if compared to other restaurants.  I like the fish (fragrant grilled fish) which was fresh , just the soup was a bit salty.
Anyway, I will definitely come back again to try other dishes!

Qi Lin Xuan Kitchen ÔºàÈ∫íÈ∫üËΩ©Â∞èÂé®ÔºâBlk 442 Jurong West

We were there to celebrate birthdays. There were 8 of us and we ordered the set menu for 8 to 10 persons. The eight dishes we had included omelette, prawn, curry fish head, chicken, pork, squid, vegetables and beancurd. It was a good meal for following reasons:
- delicious
- friendly and enthusiastic team of staff
- value for money
- comfortable dining environment

The portion was huge and eash dish was nicely cooked and presented.

We will dine at this ‚Äòtze char‚Äô stall frequently.

This was my second visit to Summer Pavilion, and once again, it exceeded expectations. The refined ambience and elegant interior design create a serene setting perfect for an intimate dining experience. ‚Ä¶

Was there on porridge night. Food was basic but wholesome. Nothing to get excited about but quantity was good and everthing was clean and well presented. It was a fair meal for the price which was $14 per adult for the buffet. Quality of the dessert cakes was better for a small selection. Overall worth supporting as a social enterprise but if it were a pure commercial endeavour I would say 50/50. May not do back if there ere nearby options. But might go if in the vicinity and feeling like porridge.

I‚Äôm uncertain about the Korean flavour of this dish but it sure has the essential element of local zi char [a.k.a. stir-fry] cooking ‚Äî tender and flavourful beef slices with onions on a sizzling cast iron hot plate with the distinctive ‚Äòwok hei‚Äô [a.k.a. smoky flavour].
P.S. Did I mention that this set that comes in generous portion and free-flow of barley tea cost below SGD8?!

Took literally 20 minutes to get a seat when there were only 2 people in front of me. Service slow for a shop which is rather small. Very disorganised and hard to get attention of staff. Order came after 15 minutes.

Food quality not as good before.

For this price and service for ramen and kaarage set, I would recommend other places.

Wanderlust place for Indian food. I really enjoyed the naan and Gobi Manchurian. They were amazingly crisp and delicious. They had a slight crunch to it. Along with that, they were perfectly seasoned. For the naan I opted for a naan basket which consisted of cheese naan, garlic naan and butter naan. I was astonished by the size of the servings. They were huge portions.
The paneer that accompanied the naan was actually quite sweet. So if you want a spicier version of paneer butter masala I think you should inform them.
The mushroom mutter curry was extremely flavourful and contained various spices.
The staff was amazing. She could memories all our orders profeciently even in the hectic and chaotic environment!
Overall, I really enjoyed visiting this place. A good place for the huge size of the naan.

Have always been a PUTIEN fan but gotta give them only 4 stars this time round as we felt the standards have dropped slightly. The drunken cockles are 10/10 as always, a perfect little snack to kickstart the meat and whet your appetite. Tangy, spicy, garlicky‚Ä¶ just so good.

Their yellow croaker dishes are so highly raved but we were just disappointed. The fish meat turned out tender but honestly there‚Äôs not much‚Ä¶. Taste. Not worth the hype and as a personal preference, yellow croaker just has too many fine bones and such a hassle to eat.

Their lor mee and sweet & sour pork were average.

On the upside, staff was helpful and provided great service.
The bread pudding tasted like solidified creamer block but it is on the recommendation list. The worst bread pudding I‚Äôve ever had.

My wife and I had a very satisfying experience here. The staff are very skillful to please customers.
I ate Villa Franzen in Bangkok before and had a pretty bad experience with the ‚Ä¶
Nice and authentic Japanese food, unfortunately they are only open to members.
Good portion sizes for the price. Not the best Korean food I've had.

Used to dine here quite often, about 6-7 years back. We usually have our dinner here, or do the occasional takeaway. There were a few turn-offs that made us rather choose other dining options. Until recently, we decided to give them a try again as we didn't have much time for a meal. Their prices are unreasonably high, the taste & appearance of their food differs every visit (inconsistent), their utensils are not the cleanest, and the indoor seats & tables have this ''oily'' feeling that makes you uncomfortable when you sit there. Though this has changed, fast forward to 2024/2025, they have upgraded their seats, so it's not as bad anymore. However the inconsistency of their food remains, and the unreasonable prices continue to exist.
We had our dinner there recently (Feb 2025), and their maggie goreng with chicken costs $6, I was shocked when I found out about the price. I mean I'm aware of inflation and all that stuff, but to be very honest $6 sounds a little absurd. Furthermore, this area is pretty secluded, as compared to e.g. other similar stores that are near shopping malls, etc, and given the location, shouldn't the price be more affordable? I believe only the residents here as well as maybe people working at the polyclinic nearby are aware of this store. When we dined here often many years back, we used to order an item that was not on the menu, and they simply charged us at an unreasonable price, the cooking was again, inconsistent.
Another thing that I would like to add on, is that the owner of the store, when we were settling the bill, actually said to our faces that it's been a long time since we last dined here, and that we usually go to the other store in that area. Not knowing what to reply, we simply brushed it off. Their pratas used to be so bad, they had many burnt parts, but this previous visit it was actually not like that anymore. The inconsistency is still there, as one of the weekdays we went there for dinner, and we ordered the maggie goreng with chicken, was actually not bad (though it made us thirsty lol, so probably MSG or something like that) and the very next day we went there for lunch, but guess what, the noodles were wetter this time round. It tasted different from the one we had the evening before.
Please, do something about the hygiene levels at this place, as in this latest visit, I have literally seen with my own eyes, this uncle who only finished half of his plate of food, and he slowly pushed the leftovers on the plate to the other end of the table, just so the mynahs that were hanging around could eat it. One mynah walked over towards the plate, and was looking at the uncle while approaching it, and proceeded to grab a mouthful of food, before skipping away. There seems to be bird waste on the table as well. Flocks of pigeons can be seen hanging around the entrance of the store at any time of the day, and sometimes they even enter the store while there are customers eating there.

This week‚Äôs meal from Sai Kitchen in Jurong Point was outstanding. Chicken biryani was fragrant, biryani rice cooked to perfection. The curry was thick and spicy, just how we like it. Friendly staff ensured our takeaway packaging stayed hot ‚Ä¶

Great ambiance and they served very good pasta. Had the butter broth spaghetti and damn, i love it so much!

We also try the Squid Ink Risotto, Croque Madame and Cornflake chicken strip.

Forest Mushroom soup is a must have !

Early birthday celebration for our eldest son.

Enjoyed the very friendly services of Blu Kouzina Dempsey from the moment we stepped in the restaurant. All the staff ensured we were comfortable and offered us recommendations of their signature dishes.

We must say that the food were very good. The Horiatiki Salad was refreshing and serving was huge (even though we ordered only the small portion).

The pita and dips were superb, we enjoyed the humus, cod roe and eggplant dips thoroughly. So much so we wanted to order another portion of pita but the wonderful attendant suggested we held on to our order as it might be too much for us after the meat dishes.

Indeed so. After the grilled octopus and meat platter arrived, we would definitely not be able to finish the additional order of pita. And the small grilled meat serving of lamb chops, meatball, chicken and beef were rather big portion. Meat were well grilled and tasted great.

The grilled octopus was really nice, throughout our meals, we were trying to figure out how the chef could grill the octopus into such crisp and yet tender bites. No wonder the dish had been their ‚Äúbest seller‚Äù.

Fortunately our order of Baklava wasn‚Äôt  that huge as we had eaten in Turkey. But the individual piece size was just right. And not that sweet as we anticipated. The flavor of coconut and nut filling suited our taste buds. They were delicious. Of course, this cannot be consumed often (due to high sugar content - my glucose level shot up after I took just one).

Knowing that we were celebrating Alexander‚Äôs birthday, the staff arranged a complimentary cake and fruit platter for him. They even offered us complimentary shots of red sweet wine but we didn‚Äôt accept as we were non drinkers. So thoughtful of them. Thank youüôèüèª.

It was a memorable evening.
Ôøº
P.S. - while we were departing, we realized it was a ‚Äúfull house‚Äù. Yet all the staff were so attentive to every diner.

Went for weekday dinner . Place was buzzing with activity and crowd .  I could see quite a few big groups .
We got a few dishes  3 types of dip , one was Anchovy flavor which was pretty ‚Ä¶
The food was outstanding! Authentic flavors, generous portion sizes and beautifully presented. Staff was nice. We will most definitely come back here!

This restaurant was recommended by my husband‚Äôs friends and he decided to bring me here for my birthday. We definitely had a great time here. Chef will come out and explain each dish. Absolute delicious food with top-notch service. My favourite dishes are tuna salsa with prawn crackers and New Zealand Lamb Rack. We are already thinking of revisit soon.
Friendly service with many affordable and yummy choices

Had some nice zhi char food from Red Lantern to usher in the new year. A visibly popular spot where seats were sprouted beyond the restaurant vicinity and big family crowds could be seen patronizing. Their signature tofu was the highlight, soft, layered and flavorful. Otherwise dishes were good too, will recommend.

business_name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
text: Ordered first time to try this new restaurant suggested by my friend. Good and tasty food at affordable price. The dishes tasted great especially their grilled chicken, fried rice and mutton soup. Nice to have new Indian food choice in ‚Ä¶

One of the more popular vegetarian food around this area. The price was reasonable, thankfully wasn‚Äôt charged high prices, just because the food was vegetarian.
The laksa gravy although it was on the watery side, it was surprisingly good. Very flavourful. Enjoyed the gravy till the very last drop.
However for the Hor Fun, it was disappointing, especially, when you compared to the laksa, for the Hor Fun, there was no wok fragrance.
Would definitely be going back to try out other dishes.

Very lovely signature hor fun. The chicken and roman lettuce also quite good.

The place is a bit small, quite noisy, and quite a few flies inside the ‚Ä¶

Ordered the fish and chip, Passion fruit sparkling Americano and chocolate lava cake.

The fish and chip consist 2 pieces of battered fish, thin fries and salad. The fish is soft and fresh which tasted great, the fries is crispy and the salad is fresh. The batter is a bit too thick and a bit too greasy, if the batter can be a bit thinner it'll be more crispy and probably feel a bit less greasy.

The passion fruit sparkling Americano is surprisingly good, I have never tried sparkling coffee before and this drink blends surprisingly well.

The lava cake tasted great too. The cake is soft and has a very strong chocolatey taste. Would have been better if it's a bit bigger. You can also choose the flavor of ice cream that comes with it.

Overall a pleasant dining experience there.

business_name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata in Singapore
text: food is not tasty, better mookatas around

business_name: Yan Palace Restaurant (Warren Golf & Country Club)
text: Open to public. Always order the soup of the day. You won't be disappointed. Other dishes of note are the vinegar pig trotters, dim sum, roast duck, desserts etc. Dim sum is probably the best in this part of Singapore.
Price is definitely not on the low end, but still, rather affordable for a Turkish meal as compared to some stores. ‚Ä¶

Sai Kitchen at Jurong Point offers wonderful Indian fare that surpasses expectations. We tried their signature Butter Chicken, spicy vindaloo, plus naan and rice ‚Äî everything hit the mark. The flavors were authentic, spices balanced, and presentation neat. The team provided warm, efficient service. Overall dining experience was calm and comfortable. For top‚Äëquality Indian cuisine in the Jurong area, this is a stellar choice.

Had a fantastic meal at Quenino last week. The menu was well thought out, with subtle but intentional use of certain ingredients to elevate the dishes.  While Southeast Asian inspired menus are all too common these days, I appreciate how it still caters to the local palette with nuanced and complex flavours.

Service was really warm; the staff were very attentive without being intrusive.

The raving reviews do speak for itself, and I would highly recommend this place!

This is my favourite kway chap stall, very tasty & also not expensive. All the senior helpers at the stall are fast & efficient, you don't have to wait too long in the queue. Only open from Thur to Sun in the morning.

Tried their CaiPo tofu once via GradFood and came to the restaurant to try their dishes. Surprisingly all the food we ordered are quite good! Especially the red wine spare ribs! üòã Fish is great too and the portion is huge for 2 pax. The only thing I think can be improved is to reduce the waiting time. Went there at 6.25pm and food only served at 7pm.

A value for money tonkatsu ramen place. Had been here a few times, and it has never disappointed in the food department. Great tonkatsu, delish ramen with umami rich broth, and free flow of rice, and cabbage! Service is good but sometimes, ‚Ä¶

I am close to 60 and using a walking stick. I came with my 4 young adult children, second group in the queue. It would be great if seats can be offered to people of disabilities to wait for our table to be available. The food are awesome though.
Super prompt service at peak hour! Really enjoyed the food here in a convenient location

business_name: The Halia at Singapore Botanic Gardens
text: Took us a while to reach the restaurant as we walk all the way from MRT station. Greeted by friendly staffs with nice food and atmosphere. Will come again.

We had a pleasure to hold our department lunch (20 paxs) at Colony last Friday. Ambience and selection of food are great. They seated us in a private section of the restaurant which we did not expect. Freshly made pasta, laska and tiramisu and many more. Staff are attentive, helpful and friendly, especially Rudi. Will try out their seafood buffet soon. Do note that if you have a big group, advance 50% deposit is required to secure the reservation.

Don't sleep on their lei cha mee hoon kueh! Visited a couple times (big fan of their ayam penyet and nasi tumpeng) but didn't realise they had this on their menu. The flavourful umami broth and tender mee far exceeded my expectations. My ‚Ä¶

5 stars for the incredible hospitality!
One of those rare places where the service truly makes the experience. The waiters and waitresses looked genuinely happy to be there ‚Äî and it was contagious. I left after 3 hours feeling so positive and uplifted.

The food? Above average and definitely value for money. Nothing mind-blowing, but solid and enjoyable.
Would absolutely come back just for the good vibes.

business_name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata in Singapore
text: Mookata, nice BBQ pork (non-halal) located at Jurong East
Had the pork cutlet with rendang and a side of salad. Very nice rendang flavours and tender cutlet. Will be back

Tried this restaurant for its much raved about beef steak in many ways, of which the most interesting about this place is its 1000deg C Salamander Broiler which does the searing of its steaks.

I ordered this 800g Peter Luger style ribeye. My verdict for this steak that cost me $120.

1. The doneness was towards medium to medium well, although I was not asked how should my steak be done during ordering
2. The searing was absolutely good. Crusty, smoky sear, impressed by the machine. It's no doubt a good sear for a steak of about 2inches!
3. Could have been more generous in its seasoning. Lack of seasoning makes the overall experience lacking.
4. The steak, though its a prime ribeye Cut was way too tough for my teeth work.. For this price, I would have expected a better cut of rib eye with better marbling.

Overall, a lacklustre experience despite so much recommendations about its steak. I believe it could have been better if the chef focus on the total experience of customers eating this steak instead of just the hype of its searing with a 1000 deg C broiler.

Amazing atmosphere with amazing food. However the aircon was leaking at our first table and had to move tables. Had to also wait for quite a bit before entering as there was no one assisting us to sit. They seemed to be short staffed.
The food was really nice and cooked to perfection.
Omg what an terrible service they providing.This is second time always no good service All face like no mood to work or what ! please improve your staff customer service.

Found this restaurant from Google map and the review seem good.
The restaurant is located right inside of the HDB block, need some distance to walk from the main road.
We have ordered few of their popular dishes like curry fish head, cai pu beancurd,  beancurd pork ribs with red wine and dried shrimp french bean. We like their curry fishhead as the spice is strong, provide reasonable of vegetables and served when it hot. The fish meat tasted "fresh" and just nice for my 2 bowl of rice üòÖ. As for the cai pu beancurd, I find it is something different in preparing but tasted not very special except the fried cai pu. As for the pork ribs, the surface fried/cooked to crispy and if sauce can be more sweet will be better. French bean will not fantastic but if they can cook the bean more crispy will be great.
Overall, I will still like to recommend here for a try and their price is reasonable.

I would have to say the food and service are both excellent. The view is a bonus! Had the tasting menu. Everything was excellent
I have to say. Was a little disappointed they didn‚Äôt have omakase menu on the ‚Ä¶
Food took an hour to arrive. Each dish coming by itself. Most of the food came cold as well (lukewarm at the very best). Service was... Interesting. ‚Ä¶

Had lunch and was impressed by the exceptional service from Candy, our waitress. She was incredibly friendly, attentive, and took the time to explain the membership program in detail, making sure we understood all the benefits. Her warm and ‚Ä¶
not much crowd all the time. the lychee prawn balls. not bad but is in lychee shape not flavour. haha. jasmine green tea serve in hot only. olive rice claypot not bad. good and fast serving service.

It was delicious. I went there because a friend of mine recommended it to me. What impressed me the most was how friendly and nice the staff were. Everyone smiled and made me feel comfortable and relaxed while eating. DavidüëçüèªüëçüèªIt was a really nice place.  The portion is generous. The seasoning is just right. It's not too salty, which is nice. I didn't know that the salad came with dressing. If you don't want it, ask for it when you order. The vegetables were really fresh. My child said that the vegetables were crunchy and fresh and that they went well with sausages and meat. I was so sad that I couldn‚Äòt try a variety of dishes because I was pressed for time. Next time, I want to go and try beer too.

Visited Bollywood after a morning walk at nearby Kranji Marshes.
Ordered their nasi lemak, rojak and flat bread. The ingredients were fresh and tasty. Also saw them selling vegetables as well. Couldn't resist the freshness and bought a few bags home.
Overall is a good place for gathering.

This is a nice quiet place on weekend mornings for roti prata and masala thosai.
Prata is nice and crispy on the outside and fluffy inside. Generous serving of dal, chicken and fish curry to go with the prata.
I loved the masala thosai ..nicely sourish crispy thin and generously stuffed with spiced potato. Coconut Chutney is a bit on the watery side.

Teh Tarik is on the sweet side so the less sweet (Siu dai) is quite sweet.

The samosa is so-so though decent sized.
Friendly and helpful service.
Parking is plentiful and added convenience of picking up groceries from the nearby Fairprice.

Foods are okay, felt a bit too salty. It was quite busy as for a Sunday night. There was nice music Latina playing and adding plus to the place. Surrounded greenery view, you feel you are somewhere else more than Dempsey.

business_name: Zaffron Tandoori - North Indian and Mexican Restaurant & Bar
text: Good Staff, Honours with hospitality and the food is amazingly relishing and enough for 3 people

Excellent customer service, affordable pricing for a restaurant. Membership is free and can be signed up through the qr code on the table. The points are quite generous which can be used in the future to deduct the total bill. There's also a student meal lunch where even after including top up of soup and drink, the price can be compared to food court western food if you account drink and a soup in that latter case. Here, theres even waiters serving you food and better food quality.

All service staff wore a smile n were quick to come forward to help in every little way. Thou, we order 2 dishes only, as we had dim sum tea jus before 5pm, our server, Alwin is v happy to introduce their range of "caffeine free" tea to help digest our "dim sum".

Sydney brought us samples of 2 other dishes and the Har Cheong pork belly is the best!
Being locals who grew up in SG from 70-80's, the nostalgic inside view of the hotel lifts n rooms, as we sat at the "outdoors" area, jus reminded us of the grandeur of hotels from the last century fused with modern upgrades.

The neo-Nordic cuisine had its highlights, and my favourite dish of the evening was the chawanmushi with caviar - delicate, comforting, and luxurious. Some dishes leaned towards tartness, likely due to fermentation and preservation techniques, which is characteristic of this style.

Got the ah-ma-kase. The standouts were probably the salad (which was a substitute that day), yeye's crab curry, and the lion head fish soup.

That said, for the most part, none of these flavours were particularly new or unique. They're really nice iterations of things that feel comforting and familiar.

To me, good set menus tell me what I want to get a la carte the next time. Great set menus are ones where I want to come back and get the set menu again. This falls under the former to me. There just isn't anything novel or unique enough, and the experience not challenging enough to do it again.

Still a good restaurant, though, and I'd definitely recommend it, just get stuff a la carte.

Al-Azhar Restaurant really needs no introduction.  It is a famous eatery that is well patronised by people from all walks of life.  Indeed, customers seem to be streaming in throughout the day and well into the night, to the wee hours of the next day.

There are so many food options - there's literally something for everyone here.  You might be overwhelmed with the vast array of choices that you have.  After you have, after careful consideration, decided what to eat, the same overwhelming choices presents itself again when you decide what to drink.

We ordered the Sizzling Rib Eye Steak ($22.90), Mutton Satay, Mutton Malasa Prata Set, and Seafood Sambal Kway Teow.

Some people like to be given options - the more the merrier.  A stall offering 100 dishes is better than a stall offering only 10 dishes, in their opinion.  Nothing wrong with that.

But as a foodie, I'd prefer to patronise a stall that specialises in one or two dishes.  That stall will sink or swim just on those dishes alone.  The stall has every incentive to ensure its own survival by mastering and serving the best possible dish, and not be a jack of all trades but master of none.

Al-Azhar serves some good stuff (prata for example), and some of its food could be quite good, provided you do not compare it to the competition. For example, their Mutton Satay is quite nice, but there were a couple of sticks of Satay that were difficult to chew because they used Mutton meat containing tendon.  Compare this with a satay specialist stall, Al-Azhar's Satay will be blown out of the water.

Bottom line:  Al-Azhar's food is nice, but not great.

Get ready to fall into the sea many times! If you've ever watched Total Wipeout (UK), this is your chance to experience something similar. My kids (7 year old, 11 year old) enjoyed themselves thoroughly. It was a real workout for me too. Staff were super accommodating and flexible, lifeguards were friendly. Easy to spend more than 1 hr there.

Will go back again at high tide when all the stations are open.

Things to note:
- Singaporeans should sign up for Sentosa Islander and get discounted tickets
- There is a minimum height and age requirement which makes sense because some of the obstacles are spaced quite far apart.
- Only life jackets are provided (somehow I thought there may be towels)
- You need to swim out to the course - younger children may be intimidated
- Nearest lockers are at the public toilets
- Some stations (the higher jumps) are closed at low tide like when we went

üá∏üá¨ Black Truffle Hainanese ‚ÄúChicken‚Äù Rice‚Ä®Star of the menu - truffle‚Äëinfused rice with plant‚Äëbased ‚Äúchicken‚Äù. It‚Äôs luxe yet familiar‚Äîa surprising twist on SG staple.
üá∏üá¨ Coconut Chendol Beancurd Pudding‚Ä®Creamy coconut pudding, pandan chendol, red beans, gula melaka‚Äîsweet, nostalgic, and silky.

business_name: Zaffron Tandoori - North Indian and Mexican Restaurant & Bar
text:
Zaffron Tandoori at Boat Quay turned out to be a great dinner spot, especially for those who enjoy classic North Indian food in a scenic setting. We were seated right by the river, with a full view of the skyline across the water, and that alone set the tone for a relaxed evening. The place fills up fast, but we got a good table and the location really adds to the experience.

We ordered a range of dishes: Zafrani Chicken Tikka, Butter Chicken, Chicken Masala, a Naan basket, and rice. The food came out nicely presented and looked exactly like what you‚Äôd hope for from a proper tandoori place. The chicken tikka was tender with just the right amount of char, and the butter chicken had a smooth, creamy sauce with a mild heat. The Chicken Masala packed more spice and depth, which balanced out the rest of the meal. The naan was fresh, fluffy, and hot‚Äîclearly made on order, and definitely one of the better naan baskets we‚Äôve had in Singapore.

Drinks included a happy hour beer mug, a glass of Ashi wine, and a couple of regular and diet cokes. Not a huge drinks list, but decent enough. The service was polite and relatively quick.

The food felt generous for a group of four, and the total came to 133 SGD including service charge. For the location and view, I think that‚Äôs fair. You‚Äôre paying a little extra for the setting, but it‚Äôs not tourist trap pricing either.

It‚Äôs worth noting that the vibe here is very casual. Tables are close together, and the menu is on display outside like at a street restaurant. That said, the food quality is surprisingly consistent with what you‚Äôd expect from a more formal setting. A lot of locals and tourists alike seemed to be enjoying their evening.

Would definitely recommend if you're craving North Indian food while in Singapore, and want to sit outdoors by the water. Go early if you want a front-row table by the river.
No taste bad packing and expensive

Such a lovely evening at Claudine! Service staff are really attentive and will go the extra mile to make sure their guests feel welcome. The food is unlike anything I‚Äôve had. From appetisers to desserts, each dish was made with such care ‚Ä¶

business_name: LiXin Teochew Fishball Noodles - Causeway Point
text: Fuss free yummy fishball noodles. Love the tomato sauce + chilli pasta base. The cook didn't skimp on the crispy pork lard as well. Didn't catch the name of the cook this afternoon who made my bowl of noodles but it was great. Note: I ordered extra noodles

Rhubarb delivered an exceptional 4-course lunch that left me thoroughly impressed with their innovative and delectable creations. Each meal starts with a complimentary tiny ice cream cone made of seaweed, yuzu gel, and minced fish, a delightful and refreshing amuse-bouche.

The first course was Himeji fish with a bonito reduction and buttermilk. The fish was incredibly fresh and clean-tasting, perfectly elevated by the sauces and sides.

Next came what Rhubarb is famous for‚Äîemulsions. We were served a celeriac root emulsion with a black truffle base, pickled shimeji mushrooms, and dusted with beetroot powder. This dish was a revelation, with the truffle notes, acidity from the shimeji, and the creamy celeriac emulsion creating a rave party in my mouth.

The main course was quail with cauliflower pur√©e, a charcoal waffle, and pomegranate sauce. The quail was juicy and tender, and when eaten with the various components, it offered a symphony of flavours and textures. The head chef personally came out to serve and explain the dish, adding a special touch to the experience.

Dessert was a creative banana masterpiece, featuring a jelly layer made of banana skin and vanilla, resting on coconut sorbet, honeycomb, and banana slices. It was a perfect end to the meal.

I had mentioned it was my partner's birthday during the reservation, and Rhubarb went above and beyond. They prepared a chocolate cake and a "dessert drawer" filled with various sweet treats, adding an extra layer of joy to our celebration.

text: Amazing experience! The food was authentic and bursting with flavor‚Äîevery dish was perfectly seasoned and beautifully presented. The cozy, vibrant atmosphere made it a great place to relax and enjoy the meal. Friendly staff added to the charm. Definitely a must-visit for anyone craving delicious Thai cuisine and a great vibe!

This bistro is a nice option around the area after we visited the Hay Dairies Farm. There were several parking lots available so it was quite convenient for people who drive but there wasn't any bus stop outside so not sure if this bistro is really catered for the public or just the farm stay place.

I appreciate that the staff were friendly, polite and prompt. Food was generally good, slightly disappointed for the Char-Grilled Ribeye Hor Fun as it is not anything special which I was initially anticipating it to be because of the price. We also ordered the Crispy Prata Puffs and felt it was too oily and taste-less, although I really appreciate that the staff highlighted to me that it doesn't come with any sauce.

We really really enjoy the dessert - Warm Chocolate Lava Cake with Vanilla Ice Cream. The lava cake was perfectly warm and lava. We really enjoyed it and put a sweet end to our meal.

Amazing food, especially the Ceviche which is the best I've tasted in Singapore. The tuna tostada was also tasty and balanced.  The duck taco had a weird taste as they put pineapple salsa.  Gives it a plastic taste, so order only if you like this combination of duck and pineapple.  The prawn omelette was very tasty but felt overwhelming with strong flavours in the egg (probably milk and butter) and strong flavour in the prawns with adobo sauce.  We ordered the Valentines Day special pesto pasta and that was a winner.  Loved the chewy bite of the pasta and the light taste of the sauce.

If you‚Äôre looking for a fine meal, you‚Äôll find many places in üá∏üá¨. But if you‚Äôre looking to have a memorable experience, to feel, think, and reimagine through delicious food that surprises you, then you‚Äôll find yourself at Nouri - the older sister of Appetite (where we visited a couple times now.)

Crossroads cooking is the ethos at Nouri, rooted in the belief that cultures do not exist in isolation, and neither should food. It‚Äôs an idea born not just of creativity, but of research, anthropology, and compassion. Behind each dish is a long process of inquiry, sourcing, and deep listening. Chef Ivan and his team approach food as part anthropology, part philosophy, and part art, translating centuries of migration, memory, and meaning into dishes

It‚Äôs rare for every single dish in a tasting menu to be on point. Nouri did that well - some dishes hit harder than expected, both in flavour and feeling. It‚Äôs the first time I‚Äôve come close to tearing up during a meal, in the best possible way. ü•π Each dish seemingly asks: ‚ÄúWhat does this mean in your culture? What does this mean in mine?‚Äù The meal never feels intellectual for the sake of it. Instead, it feels intimate, like someone has mapped the world and found a way to serve it to you.

Special shoutout to Dominique for the book recommendations and Wyman who takes hospitality to the next level - I‚Äôve never met such an attentive and curious host! What a legend.

First time try. Overall, I enjoyed the main course and not as much the starter and the dessert.

business_name: Yi Jia Le Wah Chye Seafood Restaurant
text:
I recently dined at Yi Jia Le Wah Chye Seafood Zi Char, and I must say the dining at Âçé‰ªî was an exceptional experience. The standout feature of this place has to be the generous servings ‚Äì they are truly enormous! You definitely get excellent value for your money here.

It's not just about quantity, the quality of the food is equally impressive. Every dish I tried (Assam fish head, Har Cheong Gai - Fried chicken dish) was bursting with flavour, and the freshness of the seafood was undeniable, especially È∫¶ÁâáËôæ. The flavours were perfectly balanced, and I was particularly impressed by the skillful preparation of their dishes.

It was an ideal spot for a casual meal with friends or family. The staff were attentive and helpful, providing recommendations and ensuring our dining experience was enjoyable.

In conclusion, Yi Jia Le Wah Chye Seafood Zi Char is a must-visit for anyone who appreciates delicious food and sizable portions. I left the restaurant with a satisfied palate and a desire to return for more. This place certainly lives up to its reputation as an awesome dining destination.

The atmosphere here is calm and pleasant. We chose to sit outdoors, though the chairs were a little too low and soft, which made it uncomfortable for the lower back after a while, and a bit tricky to enjoy the meal comfortably. ‚Ä¶

text:
Came to visit for dinner at weekend. Full house but we managed to get a table. We had Gamja-tang (Hangover Soup/Pork Backbone Soup) and Bossam Set (Boiled Pork Belly Wrap).
Gamja-tang Soup was nice and flavourful, the meat was so tender and fall off the bone. Set came with white rice.
Bossam Set was good too. The pork belly was tender and well marinated. Set came with white rice, seaweed soup, lettuce wrap, radish, green chilli, and sliced garlic.
We also got 4 kinds of side dishes (banchan), and can refill too. Water and tissue is also provided.
On the other day we came to visit again and tried the Samgepsal Set (BBQ Pork Belly) which comes with rice+soup+lettuce. It was good and meat was tender and fresh, no gamey taste.
The food portion was decent, service was efficient, staff were attentive.
